        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 5:33PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 532 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Hazelton to 10 miles northeast of Linton. These
storms were nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Linton, Hazelton, Temvik, and rural areas of central Emmons County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms, and may
lead to localized flooding in low lying areas.</instruction>
